derivation.yuyuan_name: late 15th cent. (denoting a thing's existence): from French entité or medieval Latin entitas, from late Latin ens, ent- 'being' (from esse 'be')

entry.def: An entity is something that exists separately from other things and has a clear identity of its own.

example.tran: 作为一个有生命的实体的地球

example.ex: North and South will remain separate entities within a commonwealth until the year 2000.
example.tran: 南方和北方将作为一个政治联合体下的两个独立实体继续存在，直至2000年。
